---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About | n8than.dev" description="About me">
  <section class="container stagger">
    <h1 class="section-heading">About</h1>
    <blockquote class="epigraph">
      "The obstacle is the way."
      <cite>— Marcus Aurelius</cite>
    </blockquote>
    <p>
      I'm a developer based in San Diego building web applications that solve real problems for real
      people. I got here the long way around.
    </p>
    <p>
      I studied Computer Science from 2012 to 2020. During that time I struggled to build anything
      meaningful outside of coursework. Nothing I could make felt useful enough to actually pursue,
      and the motivation wasn't there. After graduating, I stepped away from development for a few
      years. Not because I gave up on it, but because I needed to live and grow first.
    </p>
    <p>
      I picked up a job at Scripps Mercy Hospital doing food service — cooking for hospital staff
      on the overnight shift, running the cafeteria by myself, and providing a place for people to
      escape into during their breaks. After a few years it got busy. People wanted my food, and
      the wait times and volume became a real problem I needed to solve.
    </p>
    <p>
      In 2024 I started building again. Instead of waiting for someone to hand me direction or
      tools, I just started solving a problem I could see. A food ordering system for the hospital
      staff I worked with. I iterated on it at least six times before deploying, rebuilding it from
      scratch each time to fully understand what I was doing and why. For the first time, I was
      making something for real users, solving a real problem.
    </p>
    <p>
      After launching in January 2026, it had over 50 active users within the first month and has
      since grown to more than 80. The impact went beyond convenience — staff no longer had to wait
      in the cafeteria for their food to be ready. Doctors, nurses, EVS workers, they could order
      from their floor and pick it up when it was done. More time back at the bedside, more time
      with patients, more time to actually eat and rest on break. A small tool, but it measurably
      improved how the staff spent their day.
    </p>
    <p>
      AI tooling, Claude Code especially, accelerated that process. Not by writing code for me, but
      by making problems less intimidating. Obscure configuration issues, cryptic build errors,
      unfamiliar APIs — things that used to mean hours of googling and guessing, I could now break
      down and understand in minutes. That shift let me spend my time on what actually matters:
      designing systems, engineering solutions, and building things — not chasing down why a config
      file isn't being read correctly. It gave me the confidence to push through projects and
      actually finish them.
    </p>
    <p>
      Now I'm building on that momentum. This portfolio, the projects in it, they're the start of
      putting my CS education to work the way I always wanted to. I'm sharpening my skills and
      looking for the right opportunity to grow further as a developer.
    </p>

    <section class="links">
      <h2>Find me online</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <a href="https://github.com/Nyx000" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>
        </li>
        <li><a href="mailto:hello@n8than.dev">Email</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .container {
    max-width: 42rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: var(--space-lg) var(--space-md);
  }

  .section-heading {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-md);
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-border);
    display: inline-block;
  }

  .epigraph {
    border-left: 2px solid var(--color-accent);
    padding-left: var(--space-md);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .epigraph cite {
    display: block;
    margin-top: var(--space-xs);
    font-style: normal;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }

  p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .links {
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .links h2 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .links ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .links ul a {
    display: inline-block;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-muted);
    padding: 0.5em 1.25em;
    border-radius: 9999px;
    color: var(--color-text);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition:
      border-color 0.2s ease,
      color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .links ul a:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }
</style>
